  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 7:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀκούσας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": reports of previous acts of healing had reached him.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀπέστειλε",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": there is no mention of this fact or of the second deputation (in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 7:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") in Mt.’s version. Lk. is evidently drawing from another source, oral or written.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πρεσβυτέρους τῶν Ἰουδαίων",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", elders of the Jews; the reference is probably to elders of the city rather than to rulers of the synagogue. From the designation “of the Jews” it may be inferred that the centurion was a Pagan, probably in the service of Antipas.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "διασώσῃ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", bring safely through the disease which threatened life.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
