    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 7:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ἀκούσας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "having heard",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") He had not yet seen Jesus.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πρεσβυτέρους",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "elders",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") These, though they were not destitute of faith, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 7:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", yet had less faith than he by whom they were being sent, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 7:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Yet nevertheless it is not in vain that they ask in his behalf. [The benefits of Christ at that time appertained especially to the Jews: hence it was becomingly that the Jews in this case acted as intercessors.—V. g.] Often those who have little weight of influence with God, have more power to be of service to others, who are their superiors, than to themselves.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
