  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 3.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And when he heard of Jesus;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " better rendered, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "having heard about Jesus.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " His fame as a good Physician, such as never had arisen before, coupled with his reputation as a Teacher, had now travelled far and wide. The devout centurion probably had watched with extreme interest the career of the strange and remarkable Teacher-Prophet who had risen up among the people, and had apparently (see note on ver. 7) made up his mind that this Jesus was no mortal man. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "He sent unto him the elders of the Jews, beseeching him that he would come and heal his servant;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " better rendered ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "elders",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " without the article; that is, some of the official elders connected with his own synagogue. These would be able, with more grace than himself, to plead his cause with the Master, telling him how well the centurion had deserved any assistance which a Jewish physician could afford him. Luke 7:3",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
